				<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>best</b></font>
			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Regarding the recent submissons on using Cords of Discord. I find that if you set up the exterior cameras far from your character, (use F9 and INSERT/DELETE), you can see anything coming from a long way away.  If you're having trouble seeing the character due to a tree/hill in the way, then using ALT (right/left arrow) will spin the view so that you can see.  This is also true for the wince/bellow/selo combo, having an exterior view lets me see just how close that beastie really is.<BR>
  Hope this helps, if ya like it use it. If ya dont.... then dont!    <BR>
 Take care and may your god go with you.<BR>
 Tomiam.<BR>
 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
