			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				If used in the right situations, Chords of Dissonance can be quite useful.  Singing it at low levels in open areas where MoBs wander about can be quite deadly, so it's no wonder many folks avoid it, but having this song is like having an extra attack and can be used in conjunction with other songs to do maximum damage whether solo or in groups.  Playing in third person external view and juggling will help prevent unwanted trains, and if you have Selo's and a drum, you can usually escape messy situations.
				</font>
			</td>

